cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a method for parametrizing Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) using tensor methods, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The focus of the paper is on Fully Convolutional Networks (FCNs), which are commonly used in computer vision tasks, indicating a potential fit for "cs.CV" (Computer Vision) as well. The proposed method involves regularization and compression of the network, which could also fall under "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) and "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on human pose estimation, which is a task in multimedia processing and could be relevant to "cs.MM" (Multimedia).
